title: Relational Key Creation
text:
import pandas as pd
from pathlib import Path


# cleaned data

CLEANED_DATA_PATH = Path("../data/clean/")

bautismos = pd.read_csv(CLEANED_DATA_PATH / "bautismos_clean.csv")
entierros = pd.read_csv(CLEANED_DATA_PATH / "entierros_clean.csv")
matrimonios = pd.read_csv(CLEANED_DATA_PATH / "matrimonios_clean.csv")

for df in [bautismos, entierros, matrimonios]:
    assert df.shape[0] > 0, "DataFrame is empty"

    with open(CLEANED_DATA_PATH / f"{df.event_type[0]}_keys.txt", "w") as f:
        for col in df.columns:
            f.write(f"{col}\n")

title: Step 2: Create Unique Values from Data
text:
Manual Data
The file data/interim/unique_places_manual.csv serves as the authoritative normalization reference for all place mentions across sacramental records. The resolution was performed manually to ensure accuracy for ambiguous toponyms such as Ishua and Pampamarca. The AuthoritativePlaceResolver class uses this file to link canonical names with their variants (mentioned_as) and resolves each canonical name using GeoNames, TGN, WHG, and Wikidata. The output (data/clean/unique_places.csv) is now the trusted lookup table for place resolution across the project.
We also added the category “administrative division” to places_types.json to be included in the geoResolver library, via placeRecognition module.
"administrative division": {
    "geonames": "A",
    "wikidata": "Q5",
    "tgn": "administrative divisions",
    "whg": "a"
  }

manual_data = '../data/interim/unique_places_manual.csv'

manual_data = pd.read_csv(manual_data)

resolver = placeRecognition.AuthoritativePlaceResolver(data=manual_data, places_map=PLACES_MAP)
result_df = resolver.resolve_places()

print("Resolved places:")
print(result_df)

title: Data Cleaning
text:
Cleaning Audit
Basic audit to ensure that the data cleaning process has been successful.

def cleaning_audit(df, name):
    audit = {}

    # General info
    audit["dataset"] = name
    audit["n_rows"] = df.shape[0]
    audit["n_columns"] = df.shape[1]

    # Missing values summary
    missing = df.isnull().sum()
    missing_percent = (missing / df.shape[0]) * 100
    audit["missing_values"] = missing[missing > 0].sort_values(ascending=False).to_dict()
    audit["missing_percent"] = missing_percent[missing_percent > 0].sort_values(ascending=False).round(1).to_dict()

    # Check for non-standard values in key columns if they exist
    columns_of_interest = ["baptism_place", "burial_place", "wedding_place",
                           "baptized_legitimacy_status", "burial_condition", "groom_condition", "bride_condition"]
    
    unique_values = {}
    for col in columns_of_interest:
        if col in df.columns:
            unique_values[col] = df[col].dropna().unique().tolist()
    audit["non_standard_values"] = unique_values

    return audit


bautismos_audit = cleaning_audit(BAUTISMOS_HARMONIZED, "Bautismos")
matrimonios_audit = cleaning_audit(MATRIMONIOS_HARMONIZED, "Matrimonios")
entierros_audit = cleaning_audit(ENTIERROS_HARMONIZED, "Entierros")

title: Data Cleaning
text:
Save Cleaned Data

clean_data_folder = Path("../data/clean/")

# Fill NaN values for consistency
BAUTISMOS_HARMONIZED = BAUTISMOS_HARMONIZED.fillna(value=np.nan)
MATRIMONIOS_HARMONIZED = MATRIMONIOS_HARMONIZED.fillna(value=np.nan)
ENTIERROS_HARMONIZED = ENTIERROS_HARMONIZED.fillna(value=np.nan)

BAUTISMOS_HARMONIZED.to_csv(clean_data_folder / "bautismos_clean.csv", index=False)
MATRIMONIOS_HARMONIZED.to_csv(clean_data_folder / "matrimonios_clean.csv", index=False)
ENTIERROS_HARMONIZED.to_csv(clean_data_folder / "entierros_clean.csv", index=False)
